  "body": "# Bug Report\n\n## Problem\n\nWhen adding a custom token with total amount in fiat > 0, we don't calculate fiat value (only token amount is displayed)\n\n#### Expected behavior\n\nFiat value calculated in added token with valid > 0 amount (until app restart)\n\n#### Actual behavior\n\nFiat value is '0' in added token with amount until app restart\n<img width=\"335\" alt=\"Screenshot 2020-02-14 at 11 37 39\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8749671/74519492-76dc8c80-4f1e-11ea-823a-79e411e7fb4d.png\">\n\n\n### Reproduction\n- Open Status and recover an account with custom tokens available (or new account - and you may add watch-only address then)\n- In `Wallet` -> `...` -> `Manage assets` -> `Add custom token` paste address of custom token (e.g. 0x016ee7373248a80BDe1fD6bAA001311d233b3CFa  which is `3X Short Bitcoin`)\n- Add watch-only address having that token (e.g. `0x3f5ce5fbfe3e9af3971dd833d26ba9b5c936f0be`) \n\n### Additional Information\n\n- Status version: `1.0.1`\n- Operating System: Android and iOS",
